</media>
<caption>Myriapods. The centipede<emphasis effect="italics"> Scutigera coleoptrata</emphasis> (a) has up to 15 pairs of legs. The North American millipede <emphasis effect="italics">Narceus americanus</emphasis> (b) bears many legs, although not a thousand, as its name might suggest. (credit a: modification of work by Bruce Marlin; credit b: modification of work by Cory Zanker)</caption>
