<para id="fs-idp73032944">Which of the following statements about insects is false?</para>
<list id="fs-idp79850192" list-type="enumerated" number-style="lower-alpha">
<item>Insects have both dorsal and ventral blood vessels.</item>
<item>Insects have spiracles, openings that allow air to enter into the tracheal system.</item>
<item>The trachea is part of the digestive system.</item>
<item>Most insects have a well-developed digestive system with a mouth, crop, and intestine.</item>
</list>
<!--<para><link target-id="fig-ch28_04_06"/>C</para>-->
</note>
